http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=3D/chronicle/archive/2001/05=
/24/M
N189126.DTL&type=3Dnews=20
To encourage Oaklanders to take advantage of renewable energy, the city wil=
l=20
waive fees and expedite plans for residents and business owners who want to=
=20
install solar panels or other alternative energy generators.=20
Previously, getting the necessary permits could take as long as eight weeks=
=20
and cost more than $1,000.=20
But under a measure proposed by Mayor Jerry Brown and approved Tuesday nigh=
t=20
by the Oakland City Council, the design review process will be waived if th=
e=20
equipment installation meets certain requirements, such as matching the pit=
ch=20
of a sloped roof. Permits will be free.=20
